# DyslexiaBuddy Website - Static Website Setup and Local Development

## Project Overview
This is a static website for DyslexiaBuddy, an AI reading coach application designed to help people with dyslexia improve their reading confidence and speed. The website features text scanning, book importing, read-aloud functionality, and virtual AI tutor chat.

## Current Status - STATIC SITE (GitHub Pages)
- Proper repository structure organized for static hosting (GitHub Pages)
- Clean file organization with assets in dedicated folders
- Production-ready index.html with improved design
- All asset paths verified for deployment
- Blog section added with SEO-optimized articles
- Hero section includes YouTube video embed and press logos section
- Interactive demo section with manual toggle (no auto-toggle functionality)
- All merge conflicts resolved, clean Tailwind CSS structure
- Pricing section: Monthly and Annual plans use "Subscribe" button text (not "Start Free Trial")

## Project Structure
```
/
├── index.html              # Main entry point (production-ready)
├── blog.html               # Blog listing page
